description: The Middle East region is in turbulence and the threshold of war more than ever. Thus, I'm writing a few sentences for the record. with the hope that it would be possible to escape the current conflict with cold intellect, away from the excitement, and with the contrivance of the decision-making authorities.
title: Cool down the space. Don't heat it

description: TEHRAN- In the early hours of Friday, April 19, Israeli agents inside Iran along with the regime's warplanes, carried out terrorist attacks against three places in our country. After these ineffective actions, mainstream Western media became abuzz with exaggerated accounts of the incidents.
title: Hasty, terrorist, and ineffective

description: TEHRAN - As Iranians began their day off on Friday morning, they were met with reports of an alleged Israeli assault on their nation's territory.
title: All for nothing

description: TEHRAN- According to Iran’s top human rights official, the West and the United States have to quit treating Israel’s terrorist attacks differently and applying different rules to them.
title: ‘U.S., West need to stop applying double standards to Israeli terrorist acts’

description: TEHRAN- The Iranian Foreign Ministry spokesman has criticized the U.S. and European leaders, together with the G7 ministers, for their inconsistent and contradictory views on the latest events in the West Asia region.
title: Iran slams Western countries ‘double standards’

description: TEHRAN- President Ebrahim Raisi asserts that Iran will cause Israel and its allies to regret the “slightest attack” in response to rumors that Tel Aviv was “making a decision to act” against the Islamic Republic.
title: Raisi says Iran made Israeli regret ‘slightest attack’

description: TEHRAN- if Israel takes any further military action against Iran, its response will be “immediate and at a maximum level,” Foreign Minister Hossein Amir Abdollahian told CNN Thursday.
title: Amir Abdollahian warns against Israeli attack on Iran

description: TEHRAN- Iranian Foreign Minister Hossein Amir Abdollahian has highlighted the ineffectiveness of several Security Council meetings, emphasizing that these gatherings have failed to put a stop to Israeli war crimes, despite widespread protests urging an end to the conflict against Gazans.
title: Tehran urges tangible measures against Israeli aggression

description: TEHRAN – The Ambassador of the Islamic Republic of Iran to Russia has reiterated Iran's stance on defense cooperation with Russia, dismissing unfounded claims about their involvement in regional conflicts.
title: Iran’s envoy affirms defense cooperation with Moscow

description: TEHRAN – The early hours of Friday started amidst a chaos of news and reports by U.S. media platforms that quoted anonymous American officials asserting that Israel had launched an attack on Iranian territory.
title: Israel receives calm responses as it ravages regional stability

description: TEHRAN - Iran's Foreign Minister, Hossein Amir Abdollahian, and his Jordanian counterpart, Ayman Safadi, convened on the sidelines of a United Nations Security Council meeting in New York on Thursday to address the pressing need to halt Israel's prolonged aggression against Palestinians in Gaza.
title: Iran, Jordan condemns Israeli aggression in Gaza, call for immediate ceasefire

description: TEHRAN – Iranians took to the streets across the country on Friday to praise Tehran’s retaliation against Israel which took place after the regime struck the West Asian nation’s embassy in Damascus.
title: Iranians hail Operation ‘True Promise’ in nationwide rallies

description: TEHRAN - French authorities have apprehended a man who reportedly threatened to detonate explosives at Iran's consulate in Paris. However, upon inspection, no explosives were found in his possession.
title: Man detained by Paris police after incident at Iran consulate

description: TEHRAN - International outcry continues to grow after the United States blocked a widely-backed Security Council resolution that would have allowed the State of Palestine to be admitted as a full United Nations member.
title: Mockery of peace

description: TEHRAN-Reports indicate Israeli officials, including Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu, have told Western diplomats that the regime will press ahead with a military invasion of Rafah.
title: Rafah braces for Israeli invasion

description: The Palestinian resistance movement Hamas has dismissed U.S. claims that it is obstructing ceasefire talks.
title: Hamas rejects U.S. claim

description: Google has fired more than two dozen employees for protesting its $1.2 billion contract to provide the Israeli government and military with cloud and artificial intelligence services.
title: Google fires more workers for protesting Israel contract

description: Police arrested more than 100 protesters on Columbia University's campus Thursday after they set up encampments to protest Israel’s war in Gaza.
title: Over 100 arrested at pro-Palestinian protest at Columbia University

description: A software engineer and blogger has challenged the Meta technology company over accusations that it is sharing users’ data in its WhatsApp messaging application with Israel to help the regime identify targets in the war on the Gaza Strip.
title: WhatsApp 'complicity' in Gaza genocide

description: Indians began voting on Friday in the world's largest election as Prime Minister Narendra Modi seeks a historic third term on the back of issues such as growth, welfare, Hindu nationalism and personal popularity.
title: World’s largest election begins

description: Russia’s signals that it is ready to negotiate on Ukraine are "not just for show," but talks with Vladimir Zelensky are off the table, as they would lead nowhere, Foreign Minister Sergey Lavrov told Russian media.
title: Lavrov: Russia ready for Ukraine talks, but not with Zelensky

description: TEHRAN - A Middle East security and nuclear policy specialist at Princeton University says “strategic patience” by Iran in the past was perceived as weakness by Israel.
title: Israel viewed Iran’s strategic patience as weakness: Princeton security analyst

description: TEHRAN – Esteghlal football team defeated Shams Azar 3-2 here on Friday to move top of the 2023/24 Iran’s Persian Gulf Pro League (PGPL), one points ahead of their archrivals Persepolis.
title: Esteghlal edge Shams Azar to go top: PGPL

description: TEHRAN - Kayhan devoted its editorial to Iran's rights and legal response to the insolent attacks by the usurping regime.
title: The end of Iran's strategic patience

description:
* A collection of fabric collages by Oria Mahmoudi is on view in an exhibition at Homa Gallery.
The exhibition will be running until May 7 at the gallery located at No. 8, Fourth Alley, Sanai St., Karim Khan Ave.
title: What’s in Tehran art galleries

description: TEHRAN-The closing ceremony of the tenth edition of the Islamic Revolution Art Week and the introduction of the Islamic Revolution Artist of the Year 1402 (March 2023-2024) took place Wednesday evening at Art Bureau in Tehran with the presence of the Minister of Culture and Islamic Guidance Mohammad-Mehdi Esmaeili, director of the Islamic Ideology Dissemination Organization (IDO) Hojjatoleslam Mohammad Ghomi, Art Bureau director Mohammad-Mehdi Dadman, and CEO of Mehr News Agency Mohammad-Mehdi Rahmati and other dignitaries.
title: 10th Islamic Revolution Art Week announces artist, event of year

description: TEHRAN- The 63rd Cartagena de Indias International Film Festival (FICCI), in Cartagena, Colombia, paid tribute to the world-renowned Iranian filmmaker Asghar Farhadi on April 18.
title: Colombia’s FICCI pays tribute to Asghar Farhadi

description: TEHRAN- Sadi, the renowned Persian poet, is considered one of the greatest literary figures in Iranian history. Born in Shiraz, Iran in the 13th century, Sadi's works have stood the test of time and continue to inspire readers around the world.
title: National Sadi Day, celebrating the poet of wisdom and compassion

description: TEHRAN - Dezful, with a record of more than 10 million visits to its touristic attractions, has become the most visited city in Khuzestan province during a month, covering Nowruz and Eid al-Fitr holidays.
title: Khuzestan's Dezful shines as premier holiday destination

description: TEHRAN - The traditional jewelry of Ilam, now a province in western Iran, holds a rich history and cultural significance that has captivated the attention and admiration of people worldwide.
title: From antiquity to adornment: glimpses of Ilam’s traditional jewelry

description: TEHRAN – Situated within Iran’s Semnan province, Kalpoosh Plain stands as a testament to the breathtaking diversity of nature. Once a stop along the ancient Silk Road that connected China to Europe, this plain now captivates visitors with its vibrant colors and serene landscapes.
title: Kalpoosh Plain: a natural paradise along the ancient Silk Road

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s ambassador to Kuwait, Mohammad Toutounchi, in a meeting with the new Secretary General of the Regional Organization for the Protection of the Marine Environment (ROPME), Mohammed Al-Ahmad, conferred on ways to expand environmental cooperation between the two countries.
title: Iran, Kuwait discuss ways to further environmental ties

description: TEHRAN –For the fourth consecutive year, Iran has ranked fourth in 2023 in the production of science in traditional medicine, according to SCImago Institution Ranking (SIR).
title: Iran remains 4th in science production of traditional medicine

description: TEHRAN –Iranian knowledge-based companies have participated in the 2024 Southeast Asian Healthcare and Pharma Show (SEACare), which was held from April 17 to 19 in Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.
title: Knowledge-based companies participate in SEACare 2024

description: TEHRAN –Iran attended the eight meeting of education ministers of the Shanghai Cooperation Organization (SCO) member states on April 18, which was hosted by Russia this year.
title: Tehran attends 8th meeting of SCO education ministers

description: TEHRAN - An official at Iran’s Ports and Maritime Organization (PMO) said the 35th edition of the World Association for Waterborne Transport Infrastructures entitled “PIANC World Congress 2024” will kick off in Cape Town, South Africa on April 29.
title: South Africa to host 35th PIANC world congress

description: TEHRAN - Iranian Oil Minister Javad Oji has said Iran recorded a 20 percent increase in oil and gas production in the previous Iranian calendar year 1402 (March 21, 2023- March 19, 2024), predicting a higher production this year.
title: Iran to set new record in oil, gas production this year

description: TEHRAN - The Germany-Iran Chamber of Commerce spoke out against new sanctions imposed on the Islamic Republic in response to its legitimate attack on Israel.
title: German-Iranian Chamber of Commerce opposes new sanctions

description: TEHRAN - President Ebrahim Raisi inaugurated the second phase of the Semnan power plant with a capacity of 366 megawatts (MW) on a visit to the province on Thursday.
title: Raisi inaugurates 2nd phase of Semnan power plant

description: TEHRAN - Highlighting the development of Iran’s petrochemical industry, the head of the country’s National Petrochemical Company (NPC) said the production capacity of the industry will reach more than 100 million tons by the end of the current Iranian calendar year (March 20, 2025).
title: Iran’s petchem output capacity to exceed 100m tons by Mar. 2025

description: TEHRAN - Iran’s first-ever charging station for E-buses has been launched in northern city of Karaj in Alborz Province.
title: Iran’s first E-bus charging station launched in Karaj

description: TEHRAN – Head coach of Iran’s women’s sitting volleyball team, Leyla Beryanian, says that the team need support to shine in Asian and world stages.
title: Leyla Beryanian: Iran’s women’s sitting volleyball need support

description: TEHRAN - A provincial Army official says the sound of an explosion that was heard in the central city of Isfahan on Friday morning was caused by the air defense shots.
title: Air defense shots fire at suspicious objects in Isfahan

description: TEHRAN – Iran’s defense systems have intercepted a number of unknown objects in the central province of Isfahan, according to the Iranian Army chief, who said no damage has been inflicted on any site in the country.
title: Air defenses fire at suspicious objects in Isfahan
